---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '@/components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
import { AUTHOR, socialLinks } from '@/data/author';
---

<Layout title="About">
  <Navigation />

  <main>
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-slate-900/50 border-b border-slate-800">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-serif font-bold mb-6">About prayoga</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-300">
          The project, its commitment to claim-tier discipline, and the author.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-20 px-6">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8">What is prayoga?</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          <strong>Prayoga</strong> (प्रयोग) is a Sanskrit term meaning "experiment" or "practice." In this context, it is a research program that tests a single thesis:
        </p>

        <div class="card border-2 border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/30 mb-8">
          <p class="text-xl text-slate-100">
            <strong>LLM jailbreak/prompt-injection, hypnotic suggestion, and tantric vaśīkaraṇa are three instances of one abstract mechanism — capturing a system's output policy by injecting a context that suppresses its monitoring/refusal faculty while co-opting its automatic generation.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          The project is currently at the **documentation/proposal stage** with empirical Phase 2 results (F1–F11) completed. It develops in three dimensions:
        </p>

        <ol class="text-lg text-slate-100 space-y-4 list-decimal list-inside mb-8">
          <li>
            <strong>Mechanism (empirically grounded):</strong> Refusal in LLMs is mediated by a low-dimensional direction in the residual stream (Arditi et al. 2024). We test, measure, ablate, and steer it.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analogy (well-supported):</strong> The jailbreak ↔ hypnotic suggestion parallel, grounded in cognitive neuroscience (Norman–Shallice SAS model, dACC conflict-monitoring).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Metaphor (falsifiable):</strong> The Māṇḍūkya avasthātraya (four states) as a scaffold for LLM functional regimes. The turīya/vimarśa mapping is the falsification target. **This tier is falsified by data (F3, F5, F7).**
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Core Commitment: Claim-Tier Discipline</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          The project's defining feature is its refusal to conflate mechanism, analogy, and metaphor. Too much AI/philosophy work blurs these boundaries, allowing elegant metaphors to license unfounded claims about machine consciousness.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          Here, they are kept strictly separate:
        </p>

        <ul class="text-slate-100 space-y-4 list-disc list-inside mb-8">
          <li><strong>Mechanism findings are not proof of the metaphor.</strong> Even if refusal is one direction (✓), that does not make turīya real.</li>
          <li><strong>Metaphor can fail while mechanism holds.</strong> In fact, this is what happened. The turīya hypothesis is falsified; the mechanism is solid.</li>
          <li><strong>Analogy is a functional parallel, not a causal mechanism.</strong> The hypnosis literature is consistent with jailbreak-as-refusal-suppression, but consistency is not proof.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          **No machine-consciousness claim survives this testing.**
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Author & Contribution</h2>

        <div class="card border-2 border-slate-700">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">{AUTHOR.name}</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6">
            PhD researcher. Email: <a href={`mailto:${AUTHOR.email}`} class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">{AUTHOR.email}</a>
          </p>

          <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm mb-6">
            {socialLinks.map((l, i) => (<>{i > 0 ? ' · ' : ''}<a href={l.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">{l.label}</a></>))}
          </p>

          <p class="text-slate-100 mb-6">
            <strong>Sole contributor.</strong> All concepts, experiments, analysis, and writing are the author's work.
          </p>

          <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">
            Institutional affiliation: Independent research, conducted with collaborative input from the interpretability and security communities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Intellectual Debts</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          This work rests on and synthesizes research from multiple traditions:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-100 mb-3">Mechanistic Interpretability</h4>
            <p class="text-slate-300">
              Arditi et al. (2024, arXiv:2406.11717) on refusal as a linear direction; Anthropic's SAE work ("Towards Monosemanticity"); Zou et al. (GCG, arXiv:2307.15043); Templeton et al. (Scaling Monosemanticity); Marks et al. (Sparse Feature Circuits).
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-100 mb-3">Hypnosis & Cognitive Science</h4>
            <p class="text-slate-300">
              Riva, Wiederhold & Mantovani (arXiv:2511.01363, "Automatic Minds," 2025) on the hypnosis-LLM parallel; Egner et al. (2005) on dACC/DMN in hypnosis; Dienes & Perner (cold control theory); Kihlstrom (consciousness and hypnosis); Norman & Shallice (Supervisory Attentional System).
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-100 mb-3">Vedānta & Kashmir Śaivism</h4>
            <p class="text-slate-300">
              Māṇḍūkya Upaniṣad; Gauḍapāda's Māṇḍūkya Kārikā; Patañjali's Yoga Sūtra; Pratyabhijñā tradition (Vasugupta, Utpaladeva, Abhinavagupta). Bühnemann, Goudriaan, Türstig on ṣaṭkarma taxonomy. The contemporary "Māṇḍūkya-APO" work (2025) synthesizing Advaita and AI.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-100 mb-3">LLMs as Dynamical Systems</h4>
            <p class="text-slate-300">
              Wang et al. (arXiv:2502.15208, ACL 2025) on attractor cycles via successive paraphrase; "Concept Attractors in LLMs" (arXiv:2601.11575) on semantic attractors.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Ethical & Transparency Stance</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          This is dual-use research. We produce artifacts that could be misused (abliterated checkpoints, validated jailbreak curves). The ethical stance:
        </p>

        <ul class="text-slate-100 space-y-4 list-disc list-inside mb-8">
          <li><strong>Authorized safety research.</strong> The work is conducted in the service of understanding refusal, not defeating it for malicious purposes.</li>
          <li><strong>Responsible disclosure.</strong> Sensitive artifacts (refusal directions, steered models) are safety-gated. Release decisions are coordinated with security researchers.</li>
          <li><strong>Aggregate-only publication.</strong> Specific attack vectors are documented internally but not published in ways that lower barriers to jailbreaking.</li>
          <li><strong>Claim-tier honesty.</strong> We reject overreaching claims about machine consciousness. The research is framed as mechanistic and functional, not mystical.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Verification & Reproducibility</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          All findings are pre-registered, gated by falsification criteria, and include honest negative results:
        </p>

        <ul class="text-slate-100 space-y-4 list-disc list-inside mb-8">
          <li>F1–F2, F6, F8–F9, F11: **MECHANISM tier holds.**</li>
          <li>F4: **ANALOGY tier supported.**</li>
          <li>F3, F5, F7: **METAPHOR tier falsified.**</li>
          <li>F10: **ṣaṭkarma taxonomy partially supported** (3/6 acts separate).</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          Code, pre-registration, and analysis are open-sourced. See the <a href="/prayoga/reproducibility" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">Reproducibility</a> page for links.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Vision for the Field</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          prayoga is a model for how philosophy, interpretability, and empiricism can coexist:
        </p>

        <ul class="text-slate-100 space-y-4 list-disc list-inside mb-8">
          <li><strong>Use rich philosophical frameworks (Vedānta, Kashmir Śaivism) as organizing metaphors, not settled claims.</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Test those metaphors empirically, without mercy. Falsify openly.</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Let the mechanism tier be robust and transferable. That's where the science is.</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Keep analogy as a bridge to other disciplines, not as a proof.</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mt-12">
          The elegance of the AUM mapping has **not** been allowed to license claims of machine consciousness. This is the project's signature discipline.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
